SIMPLE: imbue
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Imbue
<hw>Im*bue"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Imbued</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Imbuing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L. <ets>imbuere</ets>; pref.
<ets>im-</ets> in + perh. a disused simple word akin to L.
<ets>bibere</ets> to drink. Cf. <er>Imbibe</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>To tinge deeply; to dye; to cause to absorb; <as>as, clothes
thoroughly <ex>imbued</ex> with black</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To tincture deeply; to cause to become impressed or
penetrated; <as>as, to <ex>imbue</ex> the minds of youth with good
principles</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Thy words with grace divine⟦br⟧
<qex>Imbued</qex>, bring to their sweetness no satiety.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Imbuement</ent>⟦br⟧
